RENOVATION PRACTICE
Practicing reinforces the content of Renovation and restoration I.
Practice is carried out at an older building in need of restoration. Analysis of the current situation. Comparison of interference methods. Completing the renovation work.
Students keep a practice diary during the work period according to the regulations provided by the Native Construction practice guidelines (https://www.is.ut.ee/pls/ois_sso/tere.tulemast?viit=2120006) and submit a proper written practice report.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Acquire basic skills for restoring log constructions, reinforce and test the knowledge acquired within the course Renovation and restoration.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course students: - can estimate the reasons for damage to log structure, and make suggestions about interference methods; - can participate in log building restoration work, being independently responsible for their line of work; - acquire readiness to communicate with the commissioner and consider the specific features of the order and object.
